                    <comment id="12923560" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 19:29:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;attached is a patch with test and a sub-optimal fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll work on a better fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12923570" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 20:04:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;here&apos;s the fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the problem is if you concatenate empty with any automaton, the result must be empty.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so if the RHS was empty, the concatenation was &quot;correct&quot; but it would &lt;br/&gt;
create epsilon transitions from the LHS&apos;s accept states all to dead states...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in the fix i just return makeEmpty() if either is empty, which is a very quick check.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will commit soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12923571" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 20:08:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1026104&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
